{
  "answer": "**Yājñavalkya Smṛti, Chapter 2 (Vyavahārādhyāya)** lays down the specified interest rules in verses 37–38.[^1][^2]\n\n> An eightieth part is the interest per month when there is a pledge; otherwise, it is two, three, four, or five percent, according to the order of the *varṇa*s. // Yj_2.37 //\n\n> Those who travel through forests may pay ten percent, and those who travel by sea, twenty percent; or all persons of all castes may pay the interest they have agreed upon. // Yj_2.38 //\n\nThe immediately following verse (39) specifies the maximum recoverable interest caps matching the query.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Yājñavalkya Smṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/02/translation/#p-286928).\n\n[^2]: Yājñavalkya Smṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/02/translation/#p-36c790).\n\n[^3]: Yājñavalkya Smṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/02/translation/#p-73b94c).",
